article.description: — Drew Lowder's 15 points helped Cleveland State defeat Western Michigan 71-49 on Saturday.
article.headline: Cleveland State defeats Western Michigan 71-49
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. -- — Drew Lowder's 15 points helped Cleveland State defeat Western Michigan 71-49 on Saturday. Lowder shot 6 for 9, including 3 for 5 from beyond the arc for the Vikings (4-3). Tristan Enaruna scored 14 points and added five rebounds. Tujautae Williams shot 4 of 7 from the field to finish with eight points, while adding six rebounds and four steals. Lamar Norman Jr. finished with 13 points for the Broncos (2-5). Titus Wright added eight points, six rebounds and two blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
